==Korean==

===Adjective===
'''두껍다''' (dukkeobda, dukkeopda) 
# To be [[thick]]

====Antonyms====
* [[얇다]] (yalbda, yalpda) To be [[thin]] 

====Derived terms====
* [[두께]] (dukke) [[thickness]] cf. German [[Dicke]]

====Related terms====
* [[두꺼비]] (dukkeobi) [[toad]] 
* [[두터비]] (duteobi) (obsolete) [[toad]] cf. Old English [[tāda]], [[tādiġe]] (of unknown origin)
* [[두텁다]] (duteobda, duteopda) To be [[thick]]
* [[두툼]]하다 (dutum-hada) To be slightly [[thick]],  [[bulge]] 
* [[둑]] (dug, duk) [[dike]] cf. German [[dick]] "thick"
* [[둔]] (dun) [[dune]] cf. German [[dünn]] "thin"

